in the pokey.
-Yeah.

17:14.241 --> 17:17.036
-Feelin' good, Lieutenant?
-Use your head,
Szymanski.

17:17.036 --> 17:21.248
You think I'd reach out
to all these different people
just to jam you up?

17:21.248 --> 17:25.627
Since the night I stopped you
for that taillight, my world's
turned upside down.

17:25.627 --> 17:30.257
So today, when I.A.B.
grabs me for whackin' up
some dealer's bankroll...

17:30.257 --> 17:33.510
when I never took
a cent in my life,

17:33.510 --> 17:35.554
I don't chalk that up
to bad luck.

17:41.685 --> 17:43.979
Have you contacted
your delegate?

17:43.979 --> 17:46.065
(Chuckles)

17:46.065 --> 17:49.693
Oh, boy.
There must be a name for this.

17:49.693 --> 17:53.655
Stop imagining
conspiracy, Szymanski,
and start saving your job.

17:53.655 --> 17:55.657
You mind steppin' out,
Lieutenant?

17:57.785 --> 18:00.037
Watch 'em screw me
through the window.

18:17.304 --> 18:21.475
-He's just about
gone psycho.
-He didn't steal that money.

18:23.143 --> 18:25.562
-You're sure on that?
-Does somethin' wrong,

18:25.562 --> 18:30.025
he has to give up thinkin'
how unfair life's treated him.

18:30.025 --> 18:33.570
I don't know if I want to be
takin' that to my bosses
without searchin' his car.

18:33.570 --> 18:37.491
-Can I talk
to the other cop?
-Wanna come work with us?

18:42.412 --> 18:43.997
(Knocks)

18:50.003 --> 18:54.758
-You give us a minute?
-Arthur Fancy,
15th Detective Squad.

18:54.758 --> 18:58.262
-Hi, Lieutenant. Louis Jones.
-(FANCY)
You holdin' up all right?

18:58.262 --> 19:01.974
Keep telling myself, I didn't
do anything, I shouldn't have
anything to worry about.

19:01.974 --> 19:03.892
You want to run
the collar for me?

19:03.892 --> 19:06.228
We're on Avenue "D"
drivin' toward Second.

19:06.228 --> 19:10.649
Narcotics has a corner up
two blocks over. We wanna push
the skells in that direction.

19:10.649 --> 19:13.819
Sees us comin',
everyone books except
this one skeevy dealer.

19:13.819 --> 19:16.655
-You know Clive's
last name?
-Bell.

19:16.655 --> 19:20.701
Szymanski took the guy
into a hallway while
I secured the vehicle.

19:20.701 --> 19:24.705
I come back, Szymanski shows me
three decks of smack and $11.

19:24.705 --> 19:28.959
So we move the skell
to the radio car.
He starts yellin' he was robbed.

19:28.959 --> 19:31.962
How soon does Bell
repeat the charge
in the house?

19:31.962 --> 19:34.339
Uh, like a half hour.

19:34.339 --> 19:39.344
Holds off sayin' it till
Szymanski would've had time
to get rid of the money.

19:39.344 --> 19:41.930
-You're sure Szymanski
didn't do it?
-You think he might have?

19:43.765 --> 19:49.062
I don't. No. But I'm not about
to put my badge up for a guy
who says I'm in on a frame.

19:49.062 --> 19:51.356
-Szymanski said that
straight out?
-Hell, yes.

19:51.356 --> 19:54.026
When the Rat Squad showed up,
said you were too.

19:57.404 --> 20:00.407
Pissed you off
on a... car stop, huh?

20:00.407 --> 20:02.951
Car stop had nothin'
to do with any of this.

20:02.951 --> 20:06.163
Only had that happen to me
about 80 or 90 times.

20:19.843 --> 20:23.138
Would you mind taking
your glasses off?

20:23.138 --> 20:25.098
Hey, check 'em out,
and let's go, okay?

20:37.527 --> 20:41.740
Now, uh, you sure
you don't recognize anybody
in these arrays, huh?

20:43.533 --> 20:46.703
He's askin'
if you recognized anybody.

20:48.413 --> 20:50.499
(Scoffs)

20:50.499 --> 20:55.754
-You made that perp, didn't ya,
huh? You gutless scumbag.
-Boo got the car?

20:55.754 --> 20:58.382
You know, Nathan,
I don't really think this was
a good-faith effort here.

20:58.382 --> 21:00.550
Hey, what's good faith--
him doin' what you want?

21:00.550 --> 21:05.973
This guy robs or hurts more
people, it's on you, Daddy Kool.
Not that you give a rat's ass.

21:05.973 --> 21:09.059
-Let's go, okay.
-Many as he takes off, 10 times
that you'll beat and murder.

21:09.059 --> 21:12.312
And everyone of 'em
was innocent, huh, Big Daddy?

21:12.312 --> 21:15.023
-Never leave that out.
-Catch you on the street,
I'll cut your throat.

21:15.023 --> 21:18.860
-Hey.
-Catch me on the street, you're
gonna wish you never were born.

21:18.860 --> 21:21.697
-Let's go.
Come on, pig. Let's go!
-(All Shouting, Indistinct)

21:24.032 --> 21:26.285
-Get him outta here, boss!
-Phony hump!

21:26.285 --> 21:29.496
He's lookin' to make a buck
off leavin' a shooter
loose on the street!

21:29.496 --> 21:32.374
Let it go, Sipowicz!
Get him outta here now!

21:32.374 --> 21:36.253
Think everything's about money?
Think everyone thinks like you.
(Laughs)

21:36.253 --> 21:40.215
Yeah, yeah, yeah. That's
why I'm on the job, right?
Enormous financial benefits.

21:43.010 --> 21:46.305
That was the victim
of that street stickup.
He wasn't givin' no cooperation.

21:46.305 --> 21:50.183
We're gonna be
up all night again.

21:51.143 --> 21:53.103
(Sighs)

21:54.563 --> 21:56.565
♪

22:06.199 --> 22:09.953
Ah, hump rapper.
He makes that perp,
he won't say,

22:09.953 --> 22:14.082
so we get to sit here
all night hopin' he gets
in his buddy's car.

22:14.082 --> 22:17.044
-You're sure he picked him?
-That's why I had him
take his glasses off.

22:17.044 --> 22:19.338
It was right in his lyin' eyes.

22:20.714 --> 22:25.135
(Sighs, Scoffs)
Look at these idiots.

22:25.135 --> 22:29.056
-SIMONE:
Hey, what are they doing wrong?
-They oughta be asleep in bed.

22:29.056 --> 22:31.808
(Chuckles)

22:31.808 --> 22:35.562
-What?
-(Chuckling)
Nothin'.

22:35.562 --> 22:38.815
-(Laughing)
-What are you
laughin' about?

22:38.815 --> 22:43.403
Oh, I--
It just strikes me funny,
bein' tired.

22:43.403 --> 22:46.615
(Coughs,
Sighs Heavily)

22:46.615 --> 22:51.411
(Wheezes, Laughing)

22:53.163 --> 22:58.293
-(Snorts, Continues Laughing)
-SIMONE: Andy. Andy.

22:58.293 --> 23:01.213
The perp's good
for the passenger. Come on.

23:01.213 --> 23:04.049
(Grunting)
You got the driver.

23:04.049 --> 23:05.842
Yeah.
(Blows, Giggles)

23:13.016 --> 23:15.852
-Police. Pull the keys out.
-DRIVER:
Yo, what's goin' on, man?

23:15.852 --> 23:18.438
Get outta the car.
Outta the car! Outta the car!
Put your hands on your head.

23:20.774 --> 23:23.068
-Gun, Bobby!
-SIMONE:
Got ya.

23:23.068 --> 23:25.195
All right. Put your hands
behind your back.
Come on.

23:25.195 --> 23:27.322
-There must be
some kinda mistake.
-No mistake.

23:29.074 --> 23:31.868
-SIPOWICZ:
What's your name?
-Jermaine Brewer.

23:31.868 --> 23:35.247
-(Laughing) What's your
favorite day of the week?
-What?

23:35.247 --> 23:37.165
Forget it.
You're a collar on the gun.

23:37.165 --> 23:40.502
Andy, call for a radio car.
I'll do a car search.

23:40.502 --> 23:42.963
Yeah.
What's your favorite
ice cream?

23:42.963 --> 23:46.341
-15th Squad
to Central, okay?
-Who was the fifth president?

23:46.341 --> 23:48.844
(Radio Beeps)
(Dispatcher)
10-4, 15.

23:48.844 --> 23:50.971
-Hey, who's
the sixth president?
-Andy.

23:52.139 --> 23:54.683
SIMONE:
Yeah, we need an
available radio car...

23:54.683 --> 23:57.769
-at Six and Avenue "D."
-(Laughing)
How you doing?

24:00.939 --> 24:03.567
♪

24:23.086 --> 24:26.756
-Hmm.
-How's it goin',
Clive?

24:31.386 --> 24:35.348
Arthur Fancy.
You the head jack
around here?

24:35.348 --> 24:38.810
I always knew they had
some plans for you.

24:38.810 --> 24:42.522
Well, they got some
for you now, Clive.
Behind that cop robbin' me?

24:42.522 --> 24:46.443
Now, how they gonna prosecute me
for a little bit of contraband?

24:46.443 --> 24:49.321
-He robbed you, huh?
-$600.

24:49.321 --> 24:54.326
Oh, healthy bankroll.
But it was in transition.

24:54.326 --> 24:58.371
You know, even back in the day
when you was a cop on the beat,

24:58.371 --> 25:02.626
I figured you to be
a brother with a future.

25:02.626 --> 25:05.337
So how come you didn't book
when the cops came
up the street?

25:05.337 --> 25:08.673
(Chuckles)
Man,

25:09.633 --> 25:12.177
I ain't booked
in 10 years.

25:12.177 --> 25:16.223
All this,
"Feet don't fail me now."

25:16.223 --> 25:19.392
Well, they fails me
all the time.

25:19.392 --> 25:22.270
Well, knowin' that
like you do, Clive,

25:22.270 --> 25:25.774
it's hard to believe
you didn't have a plan
to look straight.

25:27.526 --> 25:29.861
-When breakfast?
-Why'd you take the collar?

25:29.861 --> 25:33.406
-Who you know wanna
be locked down?
-What, you owe someone--

25:33.406 --> 25:36.535
lookin' to alibi
why you didn't have
that money, huh?

25:36.535 --> 25:38.578
You got the mind
of a criminal, Arthur.

25:38.578 --> 25:40.330
You'd better get off
your story, Clive.

25:42.123 --> 25:45.669
The black cop
was watchin' their car...

25:45.669 --> 25:48.505
while the white cop
was roughing me off...

25:48.505 --> 25:51.508
and robbin' me
for my money roll.

25:51.508 --> 25:54.553
These two cops, they're
backin' each other up.

25:54.553 --> 25:57.180
They're sayin'
they were never apart.

25:57.180 --> 26:02.227
Now I.A.B.'s gonna come
down hard on you, Clive.
D.A.'ll ask for 20 years.

26:02.227 --> 26:05.855
(Scoffs)
Man, it was just a little
possession for my own use.

26:05.855 --> 26:09.442
They're saying for sale,
in proximity to a school.

26:09.442 --> 26:11.903
Oh, man. That's--
(Sputters)

26:11.903 --> 26:15.282
Tell me the play, Clive.
I'll see if I can help you.

26:16.866 --> 26:19.452
(Sighs)

26:19.452 --> 26:23.498
Man, my mouth hurts.
I got these sores...

26:23.498 --> 26:28.753
from my uppers slidin' up
and down, up and down.

26:28.753 --> 26:34.593
My woman,
she be criticizin' me
all the time.

26:34.593 --> 26:38.138
Plus she say
they be clickin'.
(Clicks Teeth)

26:38.138 --> 26:40.932
(Scoffs)
And you were holdin' 600
for someone else?

26:40.932 --> 26:43.852
A fella I do some things for.

26:43.852 --> 26:46.938
So you owed
your supplier 600.

26:46.938 --> 26:50.567
You were gonna tell him
the cop took that
when he collared you,

26:50.567 --> 26:54.154
-and then use it
to fix your teeth?
-(Sighs)

26:58.867 --> 27:00.327
(Exhales)

27:02.329 --> 27:04.164
Here come breakfast.

27:04.164 --> 27:06.166
-Clive.
-Hmm?

27:06.166 --> 27:07.917
-Clive.
-Mm-hmm?

27:07.917 --> 27:10.337
If they pull back
to simple possession,

27:10.337 --> 27:12.714
will you drop
the complaint
on the cop?

27:13.798 --> 27:15.759
(Chuckles)

27:17.302 --> 27:21.598
You're so deep into knowin'
human nature, Arthur.

27:21.598 --> 27:26.186
How come that don't
make you use dope?
Hmm.

27:28.730 --> 27:30.732
(Sighs)
On the gate.

27:39.532 --> 27:43.078
Mornin'.
So you do know Clive Bell.

27:43.078 --> 27:46.539
I started thinkin' last night,
I might've known him when
I was a cop. Came in to check.

27:46.539 --> 27:48.750
-Same guy?
-Yeah.

27:48.750 --> 27:53.004
I think he wants to
withdraw his complaint
on Szymanski.

27:53.004 --> 27:55.256
Lieutenant, I come
to take this guy
to the grand jury.

27:55.256 --> 27:58.635
You're in his cell
without permission
or even notification.

27:58.635 --> 28:00.679
I think he'll tell you
the same story he told me.

28:00.679 --> 28:03.515
Yeah, 'cause if
I put it in the report
that he withdrew it to you,

28:03.515 --> 28:06.893
then I gotta do some explaining,
and then you do.

28:06.893 --> 28:09.646
Szymanski still
refusing cooperation?

28:09.646 --> 28:13.358
Yeah.
Szymanski's screwed anyway--
piss-poor attitude.

28:14.984 --> 28:17.821
Well, I want you to know,
I'm gonna talk to him.

28:19.614 --> 28:22.158
Sometime when we both
have a few days,

28:22.158 --> 28:25.036
I'd love to find out
what the hell
this is about.

28:29.165 --> 28:32.961
Two collars here, Jermaine,
and a whole pile of evidence
lookin' you in the face.

28:32.961 --> 28:34.963
-Lawyer.
-Oh, that's how you want
to travel, huh?

28:34.963 --> 28:37.340
You were picked out
by the victim and an eyewitness.

28:37.340 --> 28:39.592
Ballistics matched
with your gun.

28:39.592 --> 28:44.055
-Ain't got your lab
open this early.
-That's a good point.

28:44.055 --> 28:48.560
All we're sayin' here, Jermaine,
cooperate before the evidence
has you in a corner.

28:48.560 --> 28:51.855
-That's when
we give it the weight.
-Lawyer.

28:53.231 --> 28:55.692
Crow Taylor, huh?

28:55.692 --> 28:59.279
-Is that "crow"
like the, uh, bird?
-Hey, that's it.

28:59.279 --> 29:02.991
Ask him questions in chirps.

29:02.991 --> 29:05.535
So, uh, you been rentin'
your car out for stickups
there, huh, Crow?

29:05.535 --> 29:08.413
-(Mumbles) I don't know.
-We got your vehicle's
got no signs of bein'...

29:08.413 --> 29:11.708
broken into, has been
I.D.'d by victims in
three separate incidents.

29:11.708 --> 29:16.337
Hmm. Hmm. You know, maybe
somebody made duplicates, or--

29:16.337 --> 29:19.799
plus--plus I lost
a spare set of keys?

29:19.799 --> 29:22.051
Somebody--
Somebody might be usin' that.

29:22.051 --> 29:26.264
Well, the only problem there is,
your man Jermaine's been
picked out for the stickups.

29:26.264 --> 29:29.601
He told us that
you rented him the car
for a hundred and fifty a night,

29:29.601 --> 29:31.936
and you knew what
he was usin' it for.

29:31.936 --> 29:33.730
Right?

29:37.317 --> 29:40.195
(Slaps Table)
Stick with the dumb act, Crow,

29:40.195 --> 29:43.114
you will do
the 15 Jermaine does.

29:43.114 --> 29:45.950
You explain your part here,
you're lookin' at 18 months.

29:50.663 --> 29:54.584
Never paid me no 150.
Paid a hundred a night.

30:03.343 --> 30:05.929
(Knocks)

30:05.929 --> 30:08.890
-What do you want?
-Why don't you come in
and shut the door.

30:13.686 --> 30:17.565
I think that dealer's
withdrawing his allegation
about you taking his money.

30:17.565 --> 30:19.818
That's good,
'cause I didn't take it.

30:19.818 --> 30:22.904
-You're wrong if you think
that ends it, Szymanski.
-No.

30:22.904 --> 30:27.283
I'm sure you've got more strings
to pull. I'll just try to keep
lookin' over both shoulders.

30:27.283 --> 30:30.578
Well, you may not be doing
that on the job if you don't
get straight with I.A.B.

30:30.578 --> 30:34.332
(Scoffs)
Those charges are wrong, and
you just said they're dropped.

30:34.332 --> 30:37.418
-And you refused a statement.
-Fifth Amendment's
only for perps?

30:37.418 --> 30:41.214
You know 15-A
exposes you to discipline.

30:41.214 --> 30:46.094
I'm finally gettin' what
this is about. You look bad
to I.A.B. off harassin' me.

30:46.094 --> 30:49.347
Use this leverage here
to make me tell them
what a great guy you are.

30:49.347 --> 30:52.225
And you know
what else, Szymanski?
I helped kill Kennedy.

30:52.225 --> 30:56.187
-And I helped kill
Martin Luther King.
-Hey. Hey. Hey. Look, look.

30:56.187 --> 30:58.147
That wasn't about race.

30:58.147 --> 31:01.067
-I'm tryin' to
get you to see--
-It's all about race,
Lieutenant.

31:01.067 --> 31:03.444
Then let's start there.

31:03.444 --> 31:07.532
Admit part of why you
broke balls at that traffic stop
was 'cause I'm black,

31:07.532 --> 31:10.034
and I'll admit
that part of why I tried
to get you transferred...

31:10.034 --> 31:13.037
to a black precinct was
'cause that pissed me off.

31:13.037 --> 31:15.290
You make it sound like
that's the end of what you did.

31:15.290 --> 31:17.208
Well, it's gotta end
somewhere, Szymanski.

31:18.835 --> 31:21.796
Now when I got your transfer
rerouted to this precinct,

31:21.796 --> 31:25.383
-I told myself,
we start with a clean slate.
-Oh, it wasn't like,

31:25.383 --> 31:29.804
"Let this Szymanski
see me every day and know
he's under my thumb."

31:29.804 --> 31:32.891
Look, I'm the boss
of a detective squad,
not uniform cops.

31:35.518 --> 31:38.438
Maybe... what you say
has some truth in it.

31:38.438 --> 31:41.941
I don't understand
everything that's
in my heart,

31:41.941 --> 31:44.694
but I promise you,
what went down
with that dealer,

31:44.694 --> 31:48.239
it had nothin' to do
with him or your new partner
bein' black.

31:48.239 --> 31:50.825
And it had nothing
to do with me,

31:50.825 --> 31:54.037
even though it turns out
I did know that dealer
a long time ago.

31:54.037 --> 31:57.040
Is that right?

31:57.040 --> 31:59.375
Szymanski,

31:59.375 --> 32:04.088
mistrusting everyone,
it only cuts you off.

32:04.088 --> 32:06.507
Now I'm not
putting I.A.B. up as
great people to trust,

32:06.507 --> 32:09.218
but that's
the situation you're in.

32:09.218 --> 32:12.847
You're innocent.
Tell them that.

32:23.316 --> 32:27.737
You weren't wrong
about that car stop.
Not a hundred percent.

32:29.364 --> 32:31.240
Let's put that behind us.

32:35.662 --> 32:40.166
Guy's been asking
for the statements,
uh, Sergeant Martens--

32:40.166 --> 32:41.960
He's who I'd reach out to.

32:43.836 --> 32:46.798
-All right.
-All right.

33:00.728 --> 33:04.148
♪

33:06.484 --> 33:09.320
SIPOWICZ:
I better not say
nothin' in there.

33:09.320 --> 33:12.281
Uh--Yeah, well,
hang back if you want.
(Yawns)

33:12.281 --> 33:14.534
Half-punchy,
zero tolerance--

33:14.534 --> 33:18.121
They're liable to
ask me what time it is,
I'll hit 'em with a board.

33:21.124 --> 33:23.167
SIMONE:
Appreciate you
comin' back, Anthony.

33:23.167 --> 33:26.754
No, no. We're here off
you lyin', saying you wasn't
callin' his probation upstate.

33:26.754 --> 33:29.298
Man, you dumb enough
to act surprised.

33:29.298 --> 33:31.300
SIMONE:
Hey, we got a leg up
on makin' this case.

33:31.300 --> 33:33.553
The only way
we can pressure this guy
is off a victim's I.D.

33:33.553 --> 33:37.807
I'm sorry, but that's
the way it lays out.
We are gonna do our jobs here.

33:37.807 --> 33:40.184
-(Switch Clicks)
-What's that about?

33:40.184 --> 33:42.687
Oh, I'm doin' my job--
prove he cooperated.

33:42.687 --> 33:46.149
I want you to say he's lookin'
at them pictures, and then
we gettin' the hell outta here.

33:46.149 --> 33:49.110
Show me the pictures.

33:49.110 --> 33:51.487
(Laughs)

33:53.573 --> 33:56.242
Hang on a second.

34:01.205 --> 34:03.666
I want you to realize
that Detective Sipowicz...

34:03.666 --> 34:06.252
is hangin' back
on this interview, which he's
doin' at his own request.

34:06.252 --> 34:09.005
-Tell him
to show me the pictures.
-Detective Sipowicz...

34:09.005 --> 34:11.841
recognizes some antagonism
between him and Anthony.

34:11.841 --> 34:14.886
Don't want it to impede
gettin' this perpetrator
off the street.

34:14.886 --> 34:17.722
Game.

34:17.722 --> 34:22.894
What he said to me, Anthony--
"Same how this kid
had bad experiences--

34:22.894 --> 34:24.896
"his uncle's death
and so forth--

34:24.896 --> 34:26.981
"I had similar experiences
growin' up:

34:26.981 --> 34:30.610
"beat up in the projects,
my father lost his eye.

34:30.610 --> 34:33.988
"I don't want my bad
experience--if that would
affect me unintentionally--

34:33.988 --> 34:37.784
I wouldn't want that
jeopardizing if this rap star
is willing to cooperate."

34:41.704 --> 34:43.498
Told you that, huh?

34:45.333 --> 34:47.418
Hmm.

34:47.418 --> 34:49.837
